django-graphiql: 0.4.4
graphene: 0.8.1

Creating and listing two queues on docker version 0.7.4:
```
$ aws --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4576 sqs create-queue --queue-name "myqueue1" --profile localstack
{
    "QueueUrl": "http://localhost:4576/123456789012/myqueue1"
}
$ aws --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4576 sqs create-queue --queue-name "myqueue2" --profile localstack
{
    "QueueUrl": "http://localhost:4576/123456789012/myqueue2"
}
$ aws sqs list-queues --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4576 --profile localstack
{
    "QueueUrls": [
        "http://localhost:4576/123456789012/myqueue1",
        "http://localhost:4576/123456789012/myqueue2"
    ]
}
```

When I run the same on 0.7.5 or higher:
```
$ aws --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4576 sqs create-queue --queue-name "myqueue1" --profile localstack
{
    "QueueUrl": "http://localhost:4576/queue/myqueue1"
}
$ aws --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4576 sqs create-queue --queue-name "myqueue2" --profile localstack
{
    "QueueUrl": "http://localhost:4576/queue/myqueue2"
}
$ aws sqs list-queues --endpoint-url=http://localhost:4576 --profile localstack
{
    "QueueUrls": [
        "http://localhost:4576/queue/myqueue2"
    ]
}
```

The account ID is no longer listed in the url, and only one queue is ever kept. Always the most recently created queue.
